1
00:00:18,620 --> 00:00:19,700
You're late.

2
00:00:20,780 --> 00:00:22,339
I'm not your employee anymore.

3
00:00:22,340 --> 00:00:23,820
I don't need to clock in on time, do I?

4
00:00:25,459 --> 00:00:27,099
Back when you worked for me,

5
00:00:27,139 --> 00:00:28,579
I never made you clock in either.

6
00:00:30,220 --> 00:00:32,699
So the ever-busy Mr. Tan asked me out

7
00:00:32,700 --> 00:00:35,059
just to check my attendance records?

8
00:00:35,099 --> 00:00:37,059
Trying to take back
my perfect-attendance bonus?

9
00:00:39,339 --> 00:00:41,579
Sounds like
you didn't check your payslip.

10
00:00:41,860 --> 00:00:43,179
There was never

11
00:00:43,180 --> 00:00:44,619
a perfect-attendance bonus.

12
00:00:45,659 --> 00:00:47,619
Then why did you ask me out?

13
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:51,659
The factory.

14
00:00:52,140 --> 00:00:53,500
I owe you an explanation.

15
00:00:53,860 --> 00:00:55,740
Things escalated too suddenly.

16
00:00:56,220 --> 00:00:57,618
When I asked to meet,

17
00:00:57,619 --> 00:00:59,100
I didn't expect you to come.

18
00:01:01,579 --> 00:01:03,220
That's a fair assumption.

19
00:01:04,579 --> 00:01:06,820
After all, you were the one
who kicked me out.

20
00:01:07,259 --> 00:01:08,618
By all logic,

21
00:01:08,619 --> 00:01:10,379
I should cut ties with you completely.

22
00:01:11,419 --> 00:01:13,500
But that would let you off too easily.

23
00:01:15,419 --> 00:01:16,459
Because

24
00:01:17,020 --> 00:01:19,099
I'm the fear buried in your heart.

25
00:01:19,540 --> 00:01:21,258
You're afraid I'll expose

26
00:01:21,259 --> 00:01:22,539
everything you've done.

27
00:01:23,779 --> 00:01:24,899
So you deserve

28
00:01:24,900 --> 00:01:27,019
to be condemned by your conscience

29
00:01:27,419 --> 00:01:28,539
day and night.

30
00:01:30,660 --> 00:01:32,498
You are indeed my deepest fear.

31
00:01:32,499 --> 00:01:34,900
But you don't understand why.

32
00:01:35,580 --> 00:01:37,659
Right now, you're standing alone
at the edge of a cliff.

33
00:01:38,059 --> 00:01:39,420
This cliff

34
00:01:39,660 --> 00:01:42,140
is a scale of good and evil
sharpened by fate itself.

35
00:01:42,820 --> 00:01:44,620
One wrong step,

36
00:01:45,460 --> 00:01:47,299
and it'll pierce your ankle,

37
00:01:47,580 --> 00:01:49,260
leaving you bleeding

38
00:01:49,460 --> 00:01:50,860
and in unbearable pain.

39
00:01:52,619 --> 00:01:53,659
Li Shujing,

40
00:01:54,419 --> 00:01:55,500
stop now.

41
00:01:56,499 --> 00:01:58,340
Don't keep digging.

42
00:01:59,540 --> 00:02:01,939
No matter who's hiding behind the board,

43
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:04,900
I will drag him into the open.

44
00:02:06,660 --> 00:02:08,179
A climber doesn't stop moving

45
00:02:08,180 --> 00:02:09,579
just because of the wind.

46
00:02:10,580 --> 00:02:12,179
Whether I walk this cliff,

47
00:02:12,419 --> 00:02:13,739
and how I walk it,

48
00:02:14,499 --> 00:02:15,859
that's my choice.

49
00:02:26,412 --> 00:02:27,659
=Secret By My Name=

50
00:02:27,660 --> 00:02:29,536
(Adapted from the novel
Hotpot Loves Tangyuan by Ye Yijian)

51
00:02:29,537 --> 00:02:31,139
=Episode 20=

52
00:02:31,140 --> 00:02:32,699
Have things been arranged
with the factory?

53
00:02:34,020 --> 00:02:36,658
Alright. You don't need to come
to the office today.

54
00:02:36,659 --> 00:02:38,379
Have someone keep an eye on Li Shujing.

55
00:02:38,460 --> 00:02:40,259
Don't let her out of your sight.

56
00:02:41,180 --> 00:02:43,020
Otherwise, start looking for a new job.

57
00:02:45,212 --> 00:02:46,720
(Liang Yusheng)

58
00:02:48,460 --> 00:02:49,780
Why is he calling?

59
00:02:53,980 --> 00:02:54,659
Hello?

60
00:02:54,819 --> 00:02:55,938
What did you do to my sister?

61
00:02:55,939 --> 00:02:57,218
What are you talking about?

62
00:02:57,219 --> 00:02:58,218
She sent me

63
00:02:58,219 --> 00:03:00,099
a strange message,
then turned off her phone.

64
00:03:00,219 --> 00:03:01,139
She said

65
00:03:01,260 --> 00:03:02,259
the wind was too strong.

66
00:03:03,619 --> 00:03:05,220
The wind was too strong?

67
00:03:05,980 --> 00:03:07,579
A climber doesn't stop moving

68
00:03:07,580 --> 00:03:08,899
just because of the wind.

69
00:03:08,900 --> 00:03:10,020
Something has happened to her.

70
00:03:12,819 --> 00:03:13,659
Who are you?

71
00:03:23,700 --> 00:03:24,620
Shujing!

72
00:03:26,619 --> 00:03:27,740
Why are you here?

73
00:03:29,020 --> 00:03:30,620
I thought you wouldn't come.

74
00:03:31,140 --> 00:03:33,180
My heart has long since
become bound to yours.

75
00:03:36,387 --> 00:03:37,466
Your heartbeat

76
00:03:37,539 --> 00:03:40,300
will betray your hiding place
with every gust of wind.

77
00:03:42,460 --> 00:03:43,580
No matter where you are,

78
00:03:45,180 --> 00:03:46,500
I'll find you.

79
00:03:48,140 --> 00:03:50,819
But you should know who kidnapped me.

80
00:03:51,499 --> 00:03:52,500
Doing this

81
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:55,180
may damage
whatever bond still exists between you.

82
00:03:56,339 --> 00:03:57,539
A bond?

83
00:03:58,099 --> 00:04:00,300
That old man has been lying there
for years.

84
00:04:00,819 --> 00:04:02,180
Did he ever think about a bond?

85
00:04:13,539 --> 00:04:14,580
Eight years.

86
00:04:14,980 --> 00:04:17,060
This is the second time
you have played this game.

87
00:04:18,580 --> 00:04:19,460
What?

88
00:04:19,819 --> 00:04:21,300
Are you planning

89
00:04:22,179 --> 00:04:23,178
to leave bite marks

90
00:04:23,179 --> 00:04:24,539
on my other collarbone as well?

91
00:04:26,859 --> 00:04:28,020
You said it yourself.

92
00:04:28,620 --> 00:04:29,659
It's been eight years.

93
00:04:30,539 --> 00:04:33,059
My methods should be
more refined by now.

94
00:04:34,299 --> 00:04:35,499
For example,

95
00:04:36,580 --> 00:04:38,299
the rope binding you today

96
00:04:38,700 --> 00:04:40,659
is not tied in a pretty bow.

97
00:04:41,179 --> 00:04:42,499
And for another,

98
00:04:45,179 --> 00:04:46,539
I prepared this as well.

99
00:04:47,299 --> 00:04:48,900
Let's talk here.

100
00:04:49,020 --> 00:04:50,659
Tell me what really happened back then.

101
00:04:52,260 --> 00:04:53,338
I already said it.

102
00:04:53,339 --> 00:04:55,020
I want everything.

103
00:04:56,460 --> 00:04:57,700
I understand you,

104
00:04:57,820 --> 00:04:59,499
just as you understand me.

105
00:05:00,099 --> 00:05:01,979
I know you're hiding something.

106
00:05:05,299 --> 00:05:06,859
What if I refuse to speak?

107
00:05:09,099 --> 00:05:10,539
Would you kill me?

108
00:05:14,179 --> 00:05:16,218
We live under the rule of law now.

109
00:05:16,219 --> 00:05:17,859
Murder is a crime.

110
00:05:18,820 --> 00:05:19,619
But

111
00:05:21,539 --> 00:05:23,099
suicide isn't.

112
00:05:25,299 --> 00:05:26,299
(Don't.)

113
00:05:32,937 --> 00:05:36,494
♪A lone bird flying
against the crowd♪

114
00:05:37,859 --> 00:05:38,658
Stop it.

115
00:05:38,659 --> 00:05:41,498
♪Shaking off the dust,
yet still circling back♪

116
00:05:41,499 --> 00:05:43,858
♪Following time's hidden veins
toward the next dawn♪

117
00:05:43,859 --> 00:05:44,780
I'll talk.

118
00:05:45,899 --> 00:05:49,657
♪Besieged by the night
sealed deep below♪

119
00:05:49,724 --> 00:05:54,698
♪As the mist clears,
searching for light's cure♪

120
00:05:54,699 --> 00:05:59,444
♪The road is narrow,
yet the way I came is not forgotten♪

121
00:05:59,820 --> 00:06:00,979
Don't lie to me.

122
00:06:07,739 --> 00:06:08,460
Uncle,

123
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:09,098
pack up now.

124
00:06:09,099 --> 00:06:10,418
Take Mrs Lin and leave together.

125
00:06:10,419 --> 00:06:11,900
My dad's men are on their way.

126
00:06:17,620 --> 00:06:18,940
You're a good kid.

127
00:06:19,140 --> 00:06:20,020
Go back.

128
00:06:20,260 --> 00:06:21,260
You're still young.

129
00:06:21,299 --> 00:06:22,600
Don't wade into this mess.

130
00:06:24,539 --> 00:06:26,560
(Bankruptcy Liquidation Agreement)
If you don't leave now, it'll be too late.

131
00:06:26,820 --> 00:06:29,019
From the moment your dad made his move,

132
00:06:29,020 --> 00:06:30,780
it was already too late.

133
00:06:32,659 --> 00:06:35,738
Mr. Li, you have to fight back.
Think about Shujing and Mrs. Li.

134
00:06:35,739 --> 00:06:36,098
They...

135
00:06:36,099 --> 00:06:37,099
Does your dad

136
00:06:37,219 --> 00:06:39,499
really plan to spare no one?

137
00:06:41,219 --> 00:06:42,419
Why?

138
00:06:43,140 --> 00:06:45,700
Why push us this far?

139
00:06:46,299 --> 00:06:47,499
Why?

140
00:06:47,700 --> 00:06:50,538
Why won't he even spare my family?

141
00:06:50,539 --> 00:06:53,019
Mr. Li. Rather than waiting for others
to grant you a way out,

142
00:06:53,020 --> 00:06:54,820
you should choose a path for them
yourself.

143
00:06:55,260 --> 00:06:56,700
There's still time to leave now.

144
00:06:58,260 --> 00:06:59,099
No.

145
00:07:00,237 --> 00:07:02,859
Once a wolf sets its sights on its prey,

146
00:07:02,979 --> 00:07:05,460
it will not stop until the hunt is over.

147
00:07:06,099 --> 00:07:07,179
Unless

148
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:09,299
the prey is dead,

149
00:07:09,580 --> 00:07:12,260
and the wolf has taken all it wants.

150
00:07:13,060 --> 00:07:13,940
Mr. Li.

151
00:07:14,859 --> 00:07:16,220
What are you trying to do?

152
00:07:16,580 --> 00:07:18,299
Only if I die

153
00:07:19,060 --> 00:07:20,179
will your dad

154
00:07:20,419 --> 00:07:22,659
spare them.

155
00:07:23,299 --> 00:07:24,940
Do you understand?

156
00:07:30,179 --> 00:07:31,299
So

157
00:07:34,179 --> 00:07:36,900
he did all of this to protect me.

158
00:07:37,739 --> 00:07:39,140
It was all because of me.

159
00:07:41,099 --> 00:07:42,259
that he died.

160
00:07:42,260 --> 00:07:46,432
♪I remember your smile again♪

161
00:07:49,175 --> 00:07:51,658
♪It has been so long
since I last saw you♪

162
00:07:51,659 --> 00:07:52,859
It wasn't your fault.

163
00:07:53,620 --> 00:07:54,859
It was mine.

164
00:07:55,179 --> 00:07:56,561
It was the Tan Group's fault.

165
00:07:56,562 --> 00:07:59,139
♪In my dreams, I crave a single embrace♪

166
00:07:59,140 --> 00:08:00,460
That's why

167
00:08:01,900 --> 00:08:04,380
you destroyed the videotape
for my sake as well.

168
00:08:10,140 --> 00:08:12,220
When a person bears too much,

169
00:08:13,580 --> 00:08:15,099
life becomes unbearably heavy.

170
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:18,499
Shujing.

171
00:08:20,979 --> 00:08:23,099
I want you to live more freely,

172
00:08:24,580 --> 00:08:26,179
even if it means hating me.

173
00:08:28,419 --> 00:08:31,700
I wonder whether the gift we prepared
has arrived at the company.

174
00:08:33,620 --> 00:08:36,619
Why have the subordinate factories
suddenly gone on strike?

175
00:08:36,620 --> 00:08:37,259
What's going on?

176
00:08:37,260 --> 00:08:39,460
Tell me about it.
What kind of factory is Fuxin anyway?

177
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:41,139
I've never heard of it.

178
00:08:42,299 --> 00:08:43,979
At such a critical moment,

179
00:08:44,340 --> 00:08:46,499
Mr. Tan is nowhere to be found?

180
00:08:46,699 --> 00:08:48,540
Who's going to take charge now?

181
00:09:09,539 --> 00:09:10,619
Mr. Tan.

182
00:09:40,419 --> 00:09:42,619
He has truly come into his own.

183
00:09:42,980 --> 00:09:44,739
He actually forced me back.

184
00:09:47,020 --> 00:09:47,818
Chairman.

185
00:09:47,819 --> 00:09:49,660
We still haven't been able
to reach Mr. Tan.

186
00:09:50,260 --> 00:09:51,139
That's not important.

187
00:09:51,140 --> 00:09:52,538
Some people care about this seat

188
00:09:52,539 --> 00:09:54,180
far more than he does.

189
00:09:55,059 --> 00:09:55,899
Vice Chairman Tan

190
00:09:55,900 --> 00:09:57,019
is still waiting for you.

191
00:09:57,299 --> 00:09:59,580
When you covet what isn't yours,

192
00:09:59,699 --> 00:10:02,139
being allowed to wait
is a kind of favor.

193
00:10:04,900 --> 00:10:06,058
What's the matter, everyone?

194
00:10:06,059 --> 00:10:08,060
Are you waiting for me to speak first?

195
